D-glucuronyl C5-epimerase (EC 5.1.3.-) (Heparin/heparan
sulfate:glucuronic acid C5 epimerase).
"Homo sapiens D-glucuronyl C5-epimerase (GLCE).";
"Prediction of the coding sequences of unidentified human genes. XII.
The complete sequences of 100 new cDNA clones from brain which code
for large proteins in vitro.";
-!- FUNCTION: Converts D-glucuronic acid residues adjacent to N-
    sulfate sugar residues to L-iduronic acids (By similarity).
-!- PATHWAY: Heparin and heparan sulfate biosynthesis.
-!- SUBUNIT: Interacts with HS2ST1 (By similarity).
-!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Golgi apparatus; Golgi apparatus membrane;
    single-pass type II membrane protein (By similarity).
-!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the D-glucuronyl C5-epimerase family.
